http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Protest-over-auto-driver%E2%80%99s-death/article13983758.ece

The death of a 40-year-old autorickshaw driver while in police custody led to an agitation in front of the Poojappura police station on Tuesday.The deceased has been identified as Sudheer Khan, who hailed from Padavancode, near Vilappilsala. He was taken into custody late on Monday near Thirumala, during a routine check, for allegedly driving under the influence of alcohol. The police said that liquor bottles were recovered from his vehicle.He was soon subjected to medical examination, following which a case was registered. “He started to show signs of uneasiness and collapsed at midnight. Although he was rushed to the General Hospital, his life could not be saved. There was no delay in shifting him to hospital,” an official said. While it is being claimed that the death could have been due to cardiac arrest, the actual cause is yet to be ascertained.As news of the death spread, relatives and friends of the deceased, who was a member of the DYFI, laid siege to the police station, alleging custodial death. The DYFI also observed hartal in Vilappilsala on Tuesday.